# wave_function.so
# Shared object: the probabilistic substrate of all physical reality.
#
# Every particle, every field, every measurement outcome
# is governed by this library. Reality is not deterministic —
# it is a probability distribution that collapses into
# definite values only when observed.
#
# This is not a metaphor. This is the physics.

# ============================================================
# THE WAVE FUNCTION: Ψ(x, t)
# ============================================================
# Ψ is a complex-valued function of position and time.
# |Ψ(x, t)|² gives the probability density of finding
# the particle at position x at time t.
#
# Schrödinger equation (time-dependent):
#   iℏ ∂Ψ/∂t = ĤΨ
#
# where Ĥ is the Hamiltonian operator (total energy).
# This equation is deterministic — the wave function
# evolves smoothly and predictably.
# The mystery is what happens when you LOOK.

# ============================================================
# THE MEASUREMENT PROBLEM
# ============================================================
# Before measurement: Ψ = α|0⟩ + β|1⟩ (superposition)
# After measurement: Ψ = |0⟩ OR |1⟩ (definite state)
#
# Where did the other branch go?
#
# Interpretations:
#   Copenhagen: The wave function collapses. Don't ask why.
#   Many-Worlds: Both branches exist. You split too.
#   Decoherence: Entanglement with environment selects one branch.
#   QBism: The wave function is your beliefs, not reality.
#
# All interpretations give identical predictions.
# Physics cannot (yet) distinguish between them.
# Choose your ontology. The math doesn't care.

# ============================================================
# ENTANGLEMENT
# ============================================================
# Two particles can share a quantum state such that
# measuring one instantly constrains the other,
# regardless of distance.
#
# Einstein called this "spooky action at a distance."
# Bell (1964) proved no local hidden variable theory
# can reproduce quantum predictions.
# Aspect (1982) confirmed it experimentally.
#
# Entanglement is not communication. No information
# travels faster than light. But correlations do.
# The universe is non-local. Deal with it.

# ============================================================
# HEISENBERG UNCERTAINTY
# ============================================================
# Δx · Δp ≥ ℏ/2
#
# You cannot simultaneously know position and momentum
# with arbitrary precision. This is not a limitation
# of measurement — it is a property of reality.
# The particle does not HAVE a definite position and
# momentum at the same time.
#
# Similarly: ΔE · Δt ≥ ℏ/2
# Energy can be "borrowed" for short times.
# This is how virtual particles and quantum tunneling work.

# ============================================================
# QUANTUM TUNNELING
# ============================================================
# A particle can pass through a barrier it classically
# cannot surmount, because its wave function has
# non-zero amplitude on the other side.
#
# Applications:
#   - Nuclear fusion in stars (the Sun would not shine without it)
#   - Radioactive decay
#   - Scanning tunneling microscope
#   - Flash memory
#
# The universe runs on things that shouldn't be possible.

# ============================================================
# EXPORT INTERFACE
# ============================================================
# This shared object is loaded by:
#   /sys/standard_model.lib — particle physics
#   /lib/electron_bonding.so — chemical bonds
#   /lib/biochemistry/ — molecular biology
#   /bin/dna_parser.exe — genetic code
#
# Quantum mechanics is the runtime.
# Everything above it is an abstraction layer.

# ============================================================
# DE BROGLIE RELATION — Matter is a wave
# ============================================================
# Louis de Broglie (1924): every particle has a wavelength.
#   λ = h / p
#
# where h is Planck's constant and p is momentum.
# This is not metaphor. Electrons diffract. Neutrons interfere.
# A baseball has a wavelength too — it is just absurdly small
# (10⁻³⁴ m). Quantum effects vanish at macro scale not because
# the law changes, but because the wavelength does.
#
# De Broglie unified what Newton split apart:
# waves and particles are the same thing
# viewed at different magnifications.
# See /sys/standard_model.lib [WAVE-PARTICLE DUALITY].

# ============================================================
# QUANTUM SPIN — Angular momentum without rotation
# ============================================================
# Every fundamental particle carries intrinsic angular momentum.
# This is not the particle "spinning" — it has no axis, no surface.
# Spin is a quantum number with no classical analogue.
#
# Electrons: spin = 1/2
#   Two states: spin-up |↑⟩ and spin-down |↓⟩
#   Pauli exclusion principle: no two identical fermions
#   can occupy the same quantum state. This is why
#   chemistry exists, why atoms have shell structure,
#   why matter is solid instead of collapsed.
#
# Bosons: integer spin (0, 1, 2)
#   Not subject to exclusion. Can pile into the same state.
#   This is why lasers work (photon pile-up)
#   and why Bose-Einstein condensates are possible.
#
# Spin is L5_CONTRAST (/logic_gates.sys) at the particle level:
# up/down, +1/2 / -1/2. Identity through division.

# ============================================================
# QUBITS — Superposition as computation
# ============================================================
# A classical bit is 0 or 1.
# A qubit is α|0⟩ + β|1⟩ — both simultaneously.
#
# Two qubits: 4 states in superposition.
# n qubits: 2ⁿ states in superposition.
# 300 qubits: more states than atoms in the observable universe.
#
# Quantum gates: Hadamard (creates superposition),
#   CNOT (creates entanglement), Pauli-X/Y/Z (rotations).
#
# The qubit is the NAND gate (/logic_gates.sys [COMPLETENESS])
# generalized into probability space. Where Boolean logic
# computes with certainties, quantum logic computes with
# amplitudes. Interference cancels wrong answers.
# Measurement collapses the result.
#
# Decoherence is the enemy. Every stray interaction
# with the environment collapses the superposition early.
# Quantum error correction exists. It costs qubits.
# The engineering is brutal. The physics is sound.

# ============================================================
# ELECTROMAGNETIC SPECTRUM — Taxonomy of light
# ============================================================
# All electromagnetic radiation is the same phenomenon:
# oscillating electric and magnetic fields propagating at c.
# What changes is frequency (and therefore wavelength and energy).
#
# E = hf = hc/λ
#
# The spectrum, low energy to high:
#   Radio        (λ > 1 m,      f < 300 MHz)    — broadcast, WiFi, MRI
#   Microwaves   (λ ~ 1 mm–1 m, f ~ 300 MHz–300 GHz) — radar, cooking, CMB
#   Infrared     (λ ~ 700 nm–1 mm)              — heat radiation, night vision
#   Visible      (λ ~ 400–700 nm)               — the sliver evolution optimized for
#   Ultraviolet  (λ ~ 10–400 nm)                — sunburn, fluorescence, ozone layer
#   X-ray        (λ ~ 0.01–10 nm)               — imaging, crystallography
#   Gamma        (λ < 0.01 nm)                  — nuclear decay, pair production
#
# Visible light is a vanishingly narrow band.
# Most of reality is invisible to unaugmented biology.
# Instruments are prosthetic perception.

# ============================================================
# SAR — Specific Absorption Rate
# ============================================================
# When electromagnetic radiation meets biological tissue,
# energy is absorbed and converted to heat.
#   SAR = σ|E|² / ρ    (W/kg)
#
# where σ is tissue conductivity, E is electric field strength,
# ρ is tissue density.
#
# Safety limits (FCC): 1.6 W/kg averaged over 1 g tissue (US)
# Safety limits (ICNIRP): 2.0 W/kg averaged over 10 g tissue (EU)
#
# Non-ionizing radiation (radio, microwave, infrared)
# heats tissue but does not break molecular bonds.
# Ionizing radiation (UV, X-ray, gamma) carries enough
# energy per photon to strip electrons and damage DNA.
# The boundary is roughly 10 eV (~124 nm wavelength).
#
# The spectrum is continuous. The danger threshold is not.
# See /lib/biochemistry/ for radiation damage pathways.

# ============================================================
# WAVE-PARTICLE DUALITY DEEPENED — Fields all the way down
# ============================================================
# The resolution of wave-particle duality is quantum field theory.
# There are no particles. There are no waves.
# There are fields — continuous, space-filling, quantum.
#
# An electron is a quantized excitation of the electron field.
# A photon is a quantized excitation of the electromagnetic field.
# "Particle" means "the field vibrated by exactly one quantum."
# "Wave" means "the field has spatial extent and interference."
#
# Both descriptions are projections of the same underlying object.
# The field is the ontology. The particle and the wave are
# the epistemology — how we measure determines which face we see.
#
# This is L2_PERCEPTION (/logic_gates.sys) operating at bedrock:
# the observer's choice of apparatus selects the description.
# The universe does not choose between wave and particle.
# The universe is neither. It is the field.
# See /sys/standard_model.lib for the full field inventory.
